      "id": "paragraph-2"
    },
    {
      "paragraphSections": [
        {
          "imgSrc": "/extras/listening/audiobooks/beginner/general/the-fireboy/paragraph-2.jpg",
          "imgAlt": "Bak and Hapu talks beside the river Nile.",
          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "Every evening they sit beside the Nile. Bak talks to his son about the factory, tomorrow's work — everything. \"One day we're going to be very rich,\" he tells Hapu. \"Are we?\" The fireboy looks into his father's tired eyes. \"Yes,\" Bak smiles. \"I don't know how and I don't know when, but we are.\" Then he stands up. \"Come on,\" he says. \"It's late. Let's go home.\""
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
