              "textEn": "Hapu is very unhappy. \"What do I do now?\" He thinks. He leaves the palace and begins to walk home. But ten minutes later he passes two men in the market. \"Cleopatra's women are coming here tomorrow morning,\" says one. \"They're arriving very early. They want to buy lots of new clothes for her.\" \"That's very good news,\" Hapu thinks."
