          "imgAlt": "Hapu goes back home and show his father some money.",
          "imgPosition": "right",
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "Hapu runs home. He is very very happy. Bak is in bed. \"Look!\" Hapu says. He shows the money from Cleopatra's necklace to his father. \"But how ...? Bak closes his eyes, then opens them again. \"I don't understand,\" he says. Hapu smiles. He sits down and tells his father everything. At the end of the story, Bak says, \"You're a good son, Hapu. Thank you.\""
            }
          ]
