          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "textEn": "At the end of Hapu's story, Cleopatra looks at him. \"All right,\" she says. \"You can go home to your father. But ...\" \"But?\" asks Hapu. \"But from today, the two of you work only for me. Do you understand?\" \"Oh yes!\" Hapu smiles. He is very happy. Now he and his father can make lots of beautiful things and be rich. \"Yes, I understand.\""
